      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "4m23 vs 6m13 is 30% performance improvement.\r\nWhen Makefile contains .NOTPARALLEL it is only the top make that runs sequentially. It prevents building multiple packages in parallel. Each individual package is still built in parallel. \r\nSome of these packages contain a lot more files than 9. In this situation -j with a value comparable to the number of source files in a package should make a bigger difference. Provided the hardware can run this many processes.",
